<h3 id="some-final-notes">Â Some final notes</h3>

<ul>
  <li>To make the above script working, youâ€™ll need my SMAHouseKeeping PowerShell module, which is available on <a href="https://gallery.technet.microsoft.com/Module-to-troubleshoot-and-ebafca16" target="_blank">TechNet here</a>.</li>
  <li>Using checkpoints inside master / long running runbooks can be key for several reasons. So Iâ€™d recommend to create manual checkpoints using the command â€œcheckpoint-workflowâ€ as often as possible, while knowing that each checkpoint requires itâ€™s space inside the SMA database.</li>
